Aere trabes, foribus cardo stridebat aenis‘Bronze was
                                the threshold with its rising steps, bronze-bound the posts, of
                                bronze the doors with their grating hinges.’ i. 448–9.;

Fulmineus Mnestheus‘They ply their spears with
                                redoubled force, both the Trojans and Mnestheus himself with the
                                flash of lightning.’;

Demisere caput, pluvia cum forte gravantur‘As when a
                                purple flower cut down by the plough pines and dies, or as poppies
                                droop their head wearily, when weighed down by the rain.’;
